OL,4,CCo-op to scrap plastic 'bags for life'
OL,5, The Co-op has become the latest
OL,6, supermarket chain to say it will stop
OL,7, selling plastic "bags for life".
OL,9,FThe retailer, which has 2,600 shops,
OL,10,Fsaid many people only used the 10p bags
OL,11,Fonce before throwing them away.
OL,13,FThe Co-op said its move would take 29.5
OL,14,Fmillion bags for life, or about 870
OL,15,Ftonnes of plastic, out of circulation
OL,16,Fevery year.
OL,18,FEarlier this month, Morrisons said it
OL,19,Fwould remove all plastic carrier bags
OL,20,Ffrom its stores over the next year.
